question.en: If you were me, what changes would you make?
question.ja_JP: あなたが私だったら、どんなことを変えますか？

question.en: How do you prefer to receive feedback?
question.ja_JP: どんな風にフィードバックを受け取りたいですか？

question.en: Do you feel you’re getting enough feedback? Why/why not?
question.ja_JP: フィードバックは十分ですか？どうしてそう思いますか？

question.en: What aspect of your job you would like more help or coaching?
question.ja_JP: 仕事のどのような面でもっと助けやコーチンがほしいですか？

question.en: How can I better support you?
question.ja_JP: どうしたらもっとあなたをサポートできますか？

question.en: What could I do as a manager to make your work easier?
question.ja_JP: マネージャとして、どうすればあなたの仕事の助けになりますか？

question.en: What is something I could do better? What feedback do you have for me?
question.ja_JP: 私の改善点は何でしょうか？私へフィードバックをお願いします。

question.en: What aspects of your work would you like more or less direction from me?
question.ja_JP: 仕事上、もっと指示が欲しいところ、逆に指示されたくないところはどこでしょうか？

question.en: What would you like to know about me?
question.ja_JP: 私について知りたいことは何でしょうか？

question.en: What do you like about my management style? What do you dislike?
question.ja_JP: 私のマネージメント方法で良いところ、悪いところはどこでしょうか？

question.en: What have your past managers done that you’d like me to also do or not do?
question.ja_JP: 以前のマネージャのやったことで、私にもしてほしいこと、逆にしてほしくないこと何ですか？

question.en: What’s your favorite thing I do as a manager of this team I should keep doing?
question.ja_JP: 私がチームのマネージャとしてしやっていることで、気に入ってること、継続すべきことは何ですか？

question.en: Where do you think I can be most helpful?
question.ja_JP: どんな場面で私は最も役に立つと思いますか？

question.en: What are your thoughts on my changes?
question.ja_JP: 私の変化についてどう思いますか？

question.en: How can I make your days more fulfilling?
What can I be doing better to help you in your job?
Are there any obstacles I can remove for you?
What can I do to help you achieve you current goals and priorities?
What can I do to make things more manageable?
How might I make this project more challenging or interesting for you?
What do you think I should know about the project, but might not?
What is the biggest challenge you are currently facing? How can I help with that?
At what point in the past week were you most frustrated with or discouraged by your work? What can I do to help you manage that?
What additional resources can I provide for you between now and the next time we meet?
I’ve noticed that our last several 1-on-1s have stayed pretty surface. What are your honest impressions of this meeting? What could we be doing differently or better?
What would you like to see change about these discussions? How could we make them more useful for you?
I’m trying to make my 1-on-1s better and would appreciate your honest feedback on this one — what did you like about it, and what could be improved?
I'd like to improve as a manager and I could really use your help. Next week, would you be willing to share some feedback on one to two things you think I could do better as your manager?
What can I do to help you enjoy your work more or remove roadblocks to progress?
Which areas would you like more or less direction from me on your work?
What are your impressions of our 1-on-1s? What could we do differently or better?
Do you think that you receive enough feedback? Is feedback helpful for your personal development? What can I do to help you get the feedback you want?
Would you like more coaching? What aspect of your job do you like more help and coaching on?
What can I do as a manager to make your work easier?
question.ja_JP: あなたの仕事をより簡単にするために、マネージャーとして私に何かできる事はありますか？

question.en: What is the percentage of my involvement in your daily tasks? Would you prefer more or less?
question.ja_JP: 日々の仕事で、私が関わっているのは何パーセントくらいでしょうか？もっと増やしたい/減らしたいですか？

question.en: What is something I could have done better? What are the situations that I could have helped more but didn’t?
question.ja_JP: 私がもっと良くできるはずだったことは何ですか？私がもっと助けになれたのはどんな場面でしょうか？

question.en: What can I do to help you?
question.ja_JP: あなたを助けるために私は何ができますか？

question.en: What is the one thing that you need the most from me?
question.ja_JP: 私を最も必要とするのはどんなことですか？

question.en: As your manager, what would you like me to stop, start, or continue doing?
question.ja_JP: マネージャーとして、私にやめてほしい/始めてほしい/続けてほしいことは何ですか？

question.en: What can I do to help remove obstacles?
question.ja_JP: 障害を取り除くために私は何ができますか？

question.en: Do you have any feedback for me?
question.ja_JP: 私に何かフィードバックはありますか？

question.en: What can I do to make your job easier?
What can I do for you that I'm not?
What can I do better or differently as your manager to support you?
How could I do a better job communicating with you?
What do you want to be doing in 5 years? 10 years? 3 years?
What are your long term goals? Have you thought about them?
What are your super powers? What powers would you like to develop?
What do you want to do in your next job?
What skills would you like to develop right now?
What additional training or education would you like?
Do you feel like you’re making progress on your big goals here? Why or why not?
What’s one thing we could do today to help you with your long term goals?
Do you feel we’re helping you advance your career at a pace you would like?
What are your big dreams in life? Are you making progress on them?
Could you see yourself making progress on more of your goals here? What would need to change to do so?
Are there any events or training you’d like to attend to help you grow your skills?
Who in the company would you like to learn from? What do you want to learn?
What can you do to take action or make progress on what we talked about today?
What can I do to take action or make progress on what we talked about today?
Where do you see your career in the next (2/5/10) years?
What work are you doing here that you feel is most in line with your long term goals?
What skills are required to reach your goals?
What are some of the work projects you’re most proud of, and what do you think you might want to do next?
What are two to three new skills you’d like to learn on the job? What about those skills interests you?
What other roles here could you see yourself in down the line? Or what areas would you like to explore?
If you were to create your ideal position, how would it differ from what you are currently doing?
How is your current work helping or hurting your professional development?
Which career or development goals do you feel like you’re not able to focus on right now?
What else can I be doing to help you grow/advance in your career?
Imagine it’s two years from now, and things have gone well: What has been your role in that? What does your role look like?
Have you given any more thought to your long-term goals since our last meeting? What are your latest thoughts?
Where do you see yourself in three years? Five years?
What professional goals would you like to accomplish in the next 6 to 12 months, and what makes you say that?
To help identify and clarify the goal: What do you want to achieve? What will you do to achieve it? When will you do it? Who do you need to involve? When should you see results?
What about this goal is important to you and what will be different when you achieve the goal?
What sort of progress have you made on the next steps we discussed last time?
What development areas do you want to work on in the coming weeks?
What actions will you take before our next 1-on-1 to make progress on X? (Also discuss and agree on actions you will take to help.)
During this meeting you’ve mentioned that you’d like to pursue X. What steps can you take toward that before our next 1-on-1?
Have you ever felt undervalued here?
What are the projects you would be interested in working on next?
How do you think about your progress on your big goals? What needs to be done to move towards the goals? What can we do to help?
Which part of the work here do you feel as most relevant to your long-term goals? What kinds of projects do you want to take part in to move toward your goals?
Do you feel like you are learning at work? What are the new things you learned lately? What are the areas you want to learn about?
Do you have the tools you need to reach your goals?
How do you think you did on your performance review this year? What do you think the results will be?
Where do you see your career in 1 year, 3 years? What can you do to make sure you reach those goals? How can we as HR help you to reach those goals (assuming the goals relate to the company)?
question.ja_JP: 1年後や3年後のキャリアについてどう考えてますか？ 思っているゴールに近づくためにあなたは何ができると思いますか？ (目標が会社に関係あることだと仮定して)私達、人事部としてあなたのお手伝いできることはありますか？

question.en: Is there a different way we can develop your skills   outside of traditional training?
What would make this your perfect job?
Are there any projects you’d really like to work on if you were given the opportunity?
What parts of your job would you like to deepen your skills in or get additional training in?
Is there an aspect of your job you would like more help or coaching?
What areas of your job do you find difficult that getting better skills at would help?
What skills do you have that you think are underutilized?
What capabilities do you want to develop?
Tell me about something new you learned since we met last.
What opportunities have you had recently to learn something new?
What would you like to learn about in the future?
What kind of training or experience would be most helpful to you right now?
What do you see as the next step in your career?
What goals have you set for your career?
How do you feel you are progressing in your career?
What big questions do you have about your career opportunities in the future?
What are your goals (for our group for you personally)
Tell me a story...
How are you? How is life outside of work?
If around a holiday: Do you celebrate [Holiday]? If so, can I ask what are you plans?
How are your parents/grandparents? Where do they live? Do you visit them?
If they have children: How is [name of child] doing? (Ask something related to their age like starting school, playing sports, or other interests.)
What do you like to do in your free time? What are your hobbies?
Who do you really admire? Why? (People often admire those they want to become)
Tell me about what you’ve been working on.
Tell me about your week – what’s it been like?
Tell me about your family/weekend/ activities?
Tell me about anything you stumbled over.
Would you update me on Project X?
question.ja_JP: Xプロジェクトで新しい情報はありますか？

question.en: Are you on track to meet the deadline?
question.ja_JP: 期限に間に合うように進んでいますか？

question.en: How is your family?
question.ja_JP: ご家族の調子はどう？

question.en: How was your weekend?
question.ja_JP: 週末はどうでした？

question.en: How’s it going?
question.ja_JP: 調子はどうですか？

question.en: So, what’s on your mind? (or Anything on your mind?)
question.ja_JP: 何か気になってることはありますか？

question.en: What would you like to start with?
question.ja_JP: 何から始めましょうか？

question.en: Hey, what’s going on?
question.ja_JP: さて、調子はどう？

question.en: Would you like to walk today, or go somewhere else outside the office?
question.ja_JP: 今日は散歩しながらとかどうでしょう？ あるいはオフィスの外でやってみるとか。

question.en: I’ve noticed you’re a little quieter than usual. Is there anything you’d like to talk about?
question.ja_JP: いつもより物静かですね？ 何か話したいことがあるのでは？

question.en: What can I do to make your day better?
question.ja_JP: あなたの一日を良くするために、私にできることはありますか？

question.en: What's something I don't know, but should?
question.ja_JP: 私が知らないけれど、知るべきことは何でしょう？

question.en: Tell me about last week.
question.ja_JP: 先週はどうでした？

question.en: What would you like to focus on at this meeting?
question.ja_JP: 今日の1on1で特に話したいことは何でしょう？

question.en: What have you been doing for fun lately?
question.ja_JP: 最近の楽しみは何ですか？

question.en: How do you feel your work/life balance is right now?
question.ja_JP: 今のワークライフバランスはどうですか？

question.en: What drives you? What motivates you to come to work each day?
question.ja_JP: あなたの原動力は何でしょう？ 毎日の仕事へのモチベーションは何でしょう？

question.en: Do you feel challenged at work? Are you learning new things?
question.ja_JP: 仕事で新しいことに挑戦できていると思いますか？ 新しいここを学んでいますか？

question.en: What’s a recent situation you wish you handled differently? What would you change?
question.ja_JP: 最近、違ったやり方で対処したかったことは何ですか？ どう変えようと思いますか？

question.en: What’s an area of your work you want to improve?
question.ja_JP: 仕事のどんな部分を改善したいですか？

question.en: How many hours a day do you feel you’re productive? How could we help you be more productive?
question.ja_JP: 1日のうち何時間くらいが生産的な時間ですか？ もっと生産的になるために、私たちはどうしたらいいでしょう？

question.en: What could I do to make you enjoy your work more?
question.ja_JP: あなたがもっと仕事を楽しむために、私にできることは何でしょう？

question.en: Do you think our company is loyal to its employees? Why or why not?
question.ja_JP: 我社は従業員に誠実だと思いますか？ どうしてそう思いますか？

question.en: What would convince you to leave for a job somewhere else?
question.ja_JP: 他の場所に就職するとしたら、その理由は何ですか？

question.en: Do you feel over-worked, under-worked, or just the right workload?
question.ja_JP: あなたの仕事量は過剰ですか？ それとも少な過ぎます？ ちょうどいいですか？

question.en: What do you like most about working on our team?
question.ja_JP: このチームで働く中で、一番好きなことは何ですか？

question.en: What do you feel is your greatest accomplishment here?
question.ja_JP: あなたがここで達成したもののうち、最高なものは何だと思いますか？

question.en: When was the time you enjoyed working here the most?
question.ja_JP: ここで働いていて、一番楽しかったのはどんなときですか？

question.en: Are you happy with your recent work? Why or why not?
question.ja_JP: 今の仕事をしていてハッピーですか？ それはどうして？

question.en: What would make you leave this job for another?
question.ja_JP: この仕事を辞めて別の場所へ行くとしたら、それはなぜでしょう？

question.en: Tell me about what you’ve learned on this project.
question.ja_JP: このプロジェクトで学んだことを教えてください。

question.en: What do you like most about your job today?
question.ja_JP: 今日の仕事で一番良かったことは何ですか？

question.en: What do you like the least?
question.ja_JP: 何より嫌いなことを教えてください。

question.en: What’s one thing about your job that, if we fixed, would make you never want to leave?
question.ja_JP: 仕事のどんな部分を直したら、あなたはここを去りたくないと思うようになるでしょうか？

question.en: What are you most excited about?
question.ja_JP: 一番ワクワクすることって何ですか？

question.en: What are you most worried about?
question.ja_JP: 一番不安なことは何ですか？

question.en: How do you think of your current workload and how are you coping with them?
question.ja_JP: 最近の仕事の負荷はどうですか？ どうやって対処しますか？

question.en: What do you need or want to accomplish and by when?
question.ja_JP: いつまでに、何を達成する必要がありますか？ あるいはしたいですか？

question.en: What feedback/praises have you been getting about your current priorities?
question.ja_JP: 現在の優先事項について、どんなフィードバックを受けていますか？

question.en: How are you feeling about your role?
question.ja_JP: 今の役割についてどのように感じていますか？

question.en: Are you happy here? What makes you say that?
question.ja_JP: ここにいて楽しいですか？　どうしてそう思いますか？

question.en: Do you feel like you're growing in your role? What makes you say that?
question.ja_JP: 今の役割で成長してる実感はありますか？　どうしてそう思いますか？

question.en: What interests you about the project(s) you’re currently working on, and why?
question.ja_JP: いまやっているプロジェクトで面白いと思う部分は何ですか？　理由も教えて下さい。

question.en: What is your favorite/least favorite thing about your work right now?
question.ja_JP: 今やっている仕事で好きなこと/好きじゃないことを教えて下さい

question.en: How do you think that least favorite thing affects your overall performance?
question.ja_JP: 好きじゃないことがあなたのパフォーマンスに影響しているとおもいますか？

question.en: What’s working well for you in your current position?
question.ja_JP: 今の役割でうまくいっていることは何ですか？

question.en: In what ways does your current position allow you to use your skills and talents?
question.ja_JP: 今の役割で、どんな風にあなたの技術と才能が使われていますか？

question.en: Which areas make you feel like your hands are tied or you are unable to reach your full potential?
question.ja_JP: どういった領域で、あなたのポテンシャルが発揮できないと感じたり、両腕を縛られているような気持ちになったりしますか？

question.en: What do you think you could be doing differently?
question.ja_JP: もっと違うやり方でできると思いますか？

question.en: If you could work on anything for the next month, what would it be? What makes you say that?
question.ja_JP: もし、来月なにかに取り組む時間があったら何をやりますか？　それはどうしてですか？

question.en: What’s one thing that could make your work more satisfying, and why?
question.ja_JP: 仕事の満足度を上げるためには何が必要だと思いますか？　その理由は？

question.en: How are you feeling about the project?
question.ja_JP: プロジェクトについてどう思いますか？

question.en: What aspect of this project has been particularly interesting for you?
question.ja_JP: あなたにとってこのプロジェクトの特に面白い部分ってどこですか？

question.en: What do you feel like you're learning from this project?
question.ja_JP: プロジェクトから何を学べていると思いますか？

question.en: What frustrates you about the project?
question.ja_JP: プロジェクトでムカつくことってありますか？

question.en: Which areas would you like to spend more time on and why?
question.ja_JP: どの領域にもっと時間を使いたいですか？　それは何故ですか？

question.en: What do you think has gone well? What do you think you could have done better? What, if anything, would you like to do, but haven't been able to?
question.ja_JP: 何がうまくいったと思いますか？　もっとうまくできたと思うことって何ですか？　やりたかったけれどもやれなかったことってありますか？

question.en: What are your biggest concerns about your current project(s)?
question.ja_JP: 現在のプロジェクトで一番の懸念点って何ですか？

question.en: I’ve noticed X about the project… Can you help me understand that better? Talk me through your process.
question.ja_JP: プロジェクトでXについて気になっているのですが、理解できるように手伝ってもらえませんか？　あなたのやり方を教えてください

question.en: Which parts of your project are unclear or confusing?
question.ja_JP: プロジェクトのどの部分が不明瞭、もしくは混乱をもたらしていますか？

question.en: What was that experience like for you?
question.ja_JP: その経験はあなたにとってどのようなものでしたか？

question.en: What did you like most/least about that?
question.ja_JP: それについて最高/最低のことってなんですか？

question.en: How did that affect you?
question.ja_JP: それはあなたにどのように影響しましたか？

question.en: How did that make you feel?
question.ja_JP: それはどのように感じましたか？

question.en: If you could change what happened, how would you alter it?
question.ja_JP: 起こったことを変えられるとしたら、何をどんな風に変えますか？

question.en: What do you think caused that to happen?
question.ja_JP: 何がそれを引き起こしたとおもいますか？

question.en: What’s your No. 1 problem right now? How are you feeling about it?
question.ja_JP: いまあなたの中での一番の問題は何ですか？　それについてどう感じていますか？

question.en: What would be the most helpful thing for you to take away from this conversation in order to make progress on it?
question.ja_JP: このやり取りの中で、事態を進展させるのに一番役に立ちそうなことは何ですか？

question.en: What have you tried so far to make progress on it?
question.ja_JP: 今の所、進捗させるためにどういうことを試しましたか？

question.en: In our last 1-on-1 you mentioned that you’d like to grow in X — how has that been going?
question.ja_JP: 前回の1 on 1でXについて成長したいといっていましたが、それの進捗はどうですか？

question.en: In our last 1-on-1 you mentioned you were frustrated by X and wanted to try Y as a solution. How has that been going?
question.ja_JP: 前回の1 on 1でXがうまく言ってなくて、解決のためにYを試してみたいといっていましたが、あれってどうなりました？

question.en: Can you name three things we can do to help so you can enjoy your job more?What is the best accomplishment you had since you are here? Do you feel appreciated for it?
question.ja_JP: 仕事がもっと楽しくできるようになるために、私達ができることを3つ挙げてください。ここにきて達成した最高の成果は何ですか？　それについてどう感じていますか？

question.en: What talents do you have that you feel we are fully utilizing?  Which of your talents are we not fully leveraging?
question.ja_JP: 「フル活用されてるな」と感じるあなたの能力はどういう部分ですか？　「全然活用されてないな」と感じるあなたの能力はどういった部分ですか？

question.en: What do you enjoy the most in your current role?
question.ja_JP: 今の役割で一番おもしろい部分は何ですか？

question.en: Happiness level, 1 to 10?
question.ja_JP: いま幸せ？　100点中何点くらい？

question.en: What’s the best part of your job?
question.ja_JP: 仕事で一番いい部分ってなに？

question.en: What’s the worst part about your job?
question.ja_JP: 仕事で最低な部分ってなに？

question.en: What’s one thing we could change about work for you that would improve your personal life?
question.ja_JP: あなた個人の人生をよりよくするために、私達が仕事で変えられるものがあるとしたら、それは何？

question.en: What did you do for fun in the past that you haven’t had as much time for lately?
question.ja_JP: 最近時間なさそうですが、時間あるときはどういうことを楽しんでいましたか？

question.en: As a kid, what did you want to be when you grew up?
question.ja_JP: 子供の頃、大人になったら何になりたかったですか？

question.en: If you had millions of dollars, what would you do every day?
question.ja_JP: 5000兆円あったら毎日なにしますか？

question.en: What questions do you have about the project?
question.ja_JP: プロジェクトに関してなにか質問はありますか？

question.en: What ideas can you bring in from past successes?
question.ja_JP: 過去の成功体験からなにかいいアイディアはありませんか？

question.en: What haven’t you tried yet?
question.ja_JP: まだ試してないことって何ですか？

question.en: What would you be doing right now if we weren’t having this meeting? How do you feel about being taken away from that task?
question.ja_JP: もしこの打ち合わせがなかったら何していましたか？ やろうとしてなかったことをできなかったことについてどう感じていますか？

question.en: How are things going for you outside of work?
question.ja_JP: 仕事以外の調子はどうですか？

question.en: Is there anything blocking you from getting your work done?
question.ja_JP: なにかブロッカーはありますか？

question.en: What area of the company would you like to learn more about?
question.ja_JP: 会社のどの領域についてもっと知りたいですか？

question.en: Are there any roles in the company you’d like to learn more about?
question.ja_JP: もっと詳細を知りたい社内の役割はありますか？

question.en: What do you think are the key skills for your role? How would you rate yourself for each of them?
question.ja_JP: あなたの役割で鍵となる技術は何だと思いますか？　あなた自身はその技術にどれくらい熟達してるとおもいますか？

question.en: Is there a situation you’d like my help with?
question.ja_JP: 私の助けが必要な場面はありますか？

question.en: What is the company not doing today that we should do to better compete in the market?
question.ja_JP: 市場で競争力を持つために、いま我社でやられていない、やるべきことはなんでしょう？

question.en: What’s one thing we’d be *crazy* not to do in the next quarter to improve our product?
question.ja_JP: プロダクトを改善するために、私達が次の四半期で絶対にやらないことはなんでしょうか？

question.en: If you were CEO, what’s the first thing you’d change?
question.ja_JP: もしあなたがCEOなら、真っ先に変えることはなんですか？

question.en: Are there any aspects of our culture you wish you could change?
question.ja_JP: あなたが変えたい、私達の文化ってありますか？

question.en: What are your favorite parts about our culture?
question.ja_JP: 私達の文化のどんなところが好きですか？

question.en: Which company values do you like the most? Which the least? Why?
question.ja_JP: 会社の価値観のどれが一番好きで、それが一番嫌いですか？　理由も教えて下さい

question.en: What is the #1 Problem at our company? Why?
question.ja_JP: 会社で一番の問題点は何でしょうか？ 理由も教えて下さい

question.en: How could we be more creative or innovative as a company?
question.ja_JP: 会社としてどうやったらもっとクリエイティブやイノベーティブになれると思いますか？

question.en: How well do you feel like you relate to you coworkers? Do you view them as friends, acquaintances, or strangers?
question.ja_JP: 同僚とどれくらいうまくいってる？　同僚をどのように見ていますか？　友人？　知人？　赤の他人？

question.en: How could we change our team meetings to be more effective?
question.ja_JP: チームの打ち合わせをもっと効果的にするにはどこを変えればいいでしょうか？

question.en: Why do you think [employee who recently quit] left? What did they tell you?
question.ja_JP: 何故 (最近退職した人) が会社をやめたと思いますか？ 彼はなにか言ってませんでしたか？

question.en: Do you feel like you’re on the same page with the team? How often do you think you need meetings to ensure you stay that way?
question.ja_JP: チームと共通の認識を持っていると思いますか？　どれくらい頻繁にそれを確認するためのミーティングを行わないといけないと思いますか？

question.en: Are there any meetings or discussions you feel you should be a part of that you’re not? Are you included in any you don’t want to be a part of?
question.ja_JP: 自分が参加するべき会議や議論がもっとあると感じますか？ 参加したくないのに巻き込まれているものはありますか？

question.en: Who would you like to work more often with? Why?
question.ja_JP: 誰ともっとよく働きたいと思いますか？　それは何故ですか？

question.en: Is everyone pulling their weight on the team?
question.ja_JP: みんながチームに集中していますか？

question.en: Who is kicking ass on the team? What have they done?
question.ja_JP: チームでいい仕事してるのはだれ？　彼は何をやった？

question.en: Who on the team do you have the most difficulty working with? Why?
question.ja_JP: チームで一番働きづらい人はだれですか？　それはどうしてですか？

question.en: Do you help other members on the team? Do others help you when you need it?
question.ja_JP: チームの他の誰かを助けていますか？　チームのメンバーはあなたが助けを必要としてるときに助けてくれますか？

question.en: Are you uncomfortable giving any of your peers constructive criticism? If so, why?
question.ja_JP: 同僚に建設的な批判を行うのは気まずいですか？　それはどうしてですか？

question.en: What’s an inexpensive thing we could do to improve our office environment for the team?
question.ja_JP: チームのオフィス環境を改善する、あまりお金のかからない方法はありますか？

question.en: Is your job what you expected when you accepted it?
question.ja_JP: あなたの仕事は内定を受諾したときに期待していたものでしたか？

question.en: Who are you friends with at work? (Shown to be a key to enjoying your job)
question.ja_JP: 職場での友人はだれですか？ (あなたの仕事を楽しくするキーパーソンを示してもらいます)

question.en: What’s something you feel is undervalued that you contribute to the team?
question.ja_JP: チームへの貢献で過小評価されていると感じている点はなんですか？

question.en: What part of your job do you wish you didn’t have to do?
question.ja_JP: あなたの仕事でやりたくないと思っている仕事はなんですか？

question.en: Who do you admire within the company and why?
question.ja_JP: 会社で尊敬している人は誰ですか？　またその理由は？

question.en: Who has really been kicking ass lately?
question.ja_JP: 一番最近で誰が一番最高の仕事をしましたか？

question.en: What do you like about working here? What’s not fun about working here?
question.ja_JP: この会社で働いていて楽しいことって何？　楽しくない部分って何？

question.en: If we could improve in any way, how would we do it?
question.ja_JP: もしとにかく改善できるのであれば、どんな風にすればいいと思う？

question.en: What’s the number one problem within our organization? Why?
question.ja_JP: この組織最大の問題はなんだと思う？　それはどうして？

question.en: What’s the biggest opportunity we’re missing out on?
question.ja_JP: 私達が逃している最大のチャンスは何だと思いますか？

question.en: What would you like to learn more about this year?
question.ja_JP: 今年、もっと学びたいことって何ですか？

question.en: Which areas would you would like more feedback on?
question.ja_JP: どの領域についてもっとフィードバックがほしいと思っていますか？

question.en: What would you like to see change here? Why do you say that?
question.ja_JP: ここで何を変えたいですか？　その理由は？

question.en: What’s the No. 1 problem with our organization, and what do you think's causing it?
question.ja_JP: この組織で最大の問題は何だと思いますか？　それは何故起きているとおもいますか？

question.en: What are we not doing that we should be doing? What makes you say that?
question.ja_JP: 私達がやるべきなんだけどやってないことって何だとおもいますか？　どうしてそう思いますか？

question.en: What are we doing that you think we should stop doing, and why?
question.ja_JP: 私達がやっていることの中で止めるべきことはありますか？　またそれは何故ですか？

question.en: How are you feeling about the company’s future overall? What makes you say that?
question.ja_JP: 会社の未来についてどう思いますか？　どうしてそう思いますか？

question.en: How would you describe the personality of the team? What sort of person would be a good fit here? What sort of person would add something we're currently missing?
question.ja_JP: チームの性格についてどんな風に表現しますか？　どういった人がチームに馴染むと思いますか？　どういった人が、チームに現在チームに欠けているものを補ってくれると思いますか？

question.en: How would you say we're doing at working together as team? What makes you say that?
question.ja_JP: チームとして一緒に働いていいることに対してどう思いますか？　またどうしてそう思いましたか？

question.en: What are some ways we could improve at teamwork? What makes you say that?
question.ja_JP: 私達のチームワークを改善するにはどうすればいいでしょうか？　またその理由は？

question.en: How would you describe the division of work among team members?
question.ja_JP: チームメンバーの仕事の分担をどのように説明しますか？

question.en: Do you feel adequately supported by other team members? What makes you say that?
question.ja_JP: 他のチームメンバーから十分なサポートを受けていると感じていますか？　どういった点でそう感じていますか？

question.en: Is there anything you’d like to see change about the team, and if so, why?
question.ja_JP: チームについてなにか見てみたい変化はありますか？　それは何故ですか？

question.en: How are you feeling about the recent news? Why do you say that?
question.ja_JP: 最近のニュースについてどう思いますか？　それについてなにか意見はありますか？

question.en: What concerns do you have about the change that haven't been addressed?
question.ja_JP: まだ対処されていない変更について、なにか懸念はありますか？

question.en: What’s going well and not so well with the new situation/development? Why do you think this might be happening?
question.ja_JP: 新しいシチュエーション/開発において何がうまく行っていて、何がうまく行っていないと思いますか？　またそれは何故起こっていると思いますか？

question.en: Do you have a clear understanding of the new goals and expectations? What makes you say that?
question.ja_JP: 新しいゴールとあなたへの期待に対して完全に理解できていますか？　どうしてそう言えますか？

question.en: How is the new situation/development affecting your work? What could be getting in the way of your being effective?
question.ja_JP: 新しいシチュエーション/開発はあなたの仕事にどんな影響がありますか？　あなたの効率を下げるものはありますか？

question.en: What sort of resources could you use right now to make things more manageable?
question.ja_JP: もっと状況をコントロールできるようにするために、今すぐ必要なリソースは何ですか？

question.en: Could you tell me a little more about that?
question.ja_JP: それについてもう少し教えてもらえますか？

question.en: Can you share some of the details around that particular issue? (Who was involved? Where? When? For how long?)
question.ja_JP: その問題についてもう少し詳細を教えてもらえませんか？ (誰が巻き込まれていますか？ いつ、どこで、どれくらいの期間？)

question.en: What are some possible ways to get the solution you need?
question.ja_JP: 必要なソリューションを得るための現実的なやり方をいくつか教えて下さい

question.en: What additional resources from me would be helpful for you as you solve this problem?
question.ja_JP: あなたがこの問題を解決するのに有用な追加のリソースってありますか？

question.en: What are your next steps to make progress on this problem?
question.ja_JP: この問題を解決するための次のステップを教えて下さい。

question.en: What do you do when you get stuck on something? What is your process of getting unstuck? Who is the team member you turn to for help?
question.ja_JP: 何かで行き詰まったときに何をやりますか？ 行き詰まりを解消するためのやり方を教えて下さい。その時あなたが助けを求めるチームメンバーはだれですか？

question.en: Who inspire you in the team? Whose opinions do you respect? What have they done?
question.ja_JP: チームでインスピレーションを与えるのはだれですか？ 誰の意見を尊重していますか？　その人は何をしましたか？

question.en: Is there anybody in the team that you find it difficult to work with? Can you tell me why?
question.ja_JP: チーム内に一緒に働きづらい人はいますか？　それはどうしてか教えてもらえますか？

question.en: What do you think about the amount of feedback in our team? When do others give feedback to you? Would you like to hear more feedback from other team member and me?
question.ja_JP: 私達のチームへのフィードバックの量についてどう思いますか？ 他の人はいつあなたにフィードバックをくれますか？ 他のチームメンバーと私からもっとフィードバックを受け取りたいと思いますか？

question.en: What do you think would help us work together better?
question.ja_JP: もっと上手に一緒に働くのに必要なことって何だと思いますか？

question.en: Whom in the team do you want to learn from? Whom do you get valuable feedback from?
question.ja_JP: チームの誰から学びたいと思いますか？　誰から価値のあるフィードバックを受け取っていますか？

question.en: What are your top three motivators?
question.ja_JP: モチベーションを上げること、トップ３を教えてください。

question.en: What excites you about our business?  The company?  What concerns you?
question.ja_JP: 私達のビジネスや会社、あなたの関心事でワクワクさせられることは何ですか？

question.en: What do you think about _________?
question.ja_JP: _________ についてどう思いますか？

question.en: What’s the No. 1 problem with our organization? Why?
question.ja_JP: うちの組織で1番の問題点って何ですか？　それは何故ですか？

question.en: Who is really kicking ass in the company? Who do you admire?
question.ja_JP: 会社でまじですごいやつは誰ですか？　あなたは誰を尊敬してますか？

question.en: Is any part of your project unclear or confusing?
question.ja_JP: あなたのプロジェクトで不明瞭だったり混乱している部分はありますか？

question.en: Has anyone on the team ever made you feel uncomfortable? What happened?
question.ja_JP: チームの中の誰かがあなたを居心地悪くしたことはありませんか？　その時は何がありましたか？

question.en: What characteristics make someone a good fit for our team? How would you look for those characteristics in an interview?
question.ja_JP: 私達のチームにピッタリ合う性格ってどんなものでしょう？　面接でそういう性格を見抜くにはどうやっていますか？

question.en: What’s the biggest thing you’d like to change about our team?
question.ja_JP: 私達のチームで変えたいと思っている最大のことって何ですか？

question.en: What’s one thing we should change about how our team works together?
question.ja_JP: チームがうまく働く上で1つだけ変えたほうがいいとすると、それはどこでしょうか？

question.en: Where do you think we can do better?
question.ja_JP: どうしたら私達はもっとうまくやれるようになると思いますか？

question.en: How would you rate our communication as a team?
question.ja_JP: チームのコミュニケーションについて評価をつけるとしたらどれくらいにしますか？

question.en: What kind of communication or information do you wish you had more of?
question.ja_JP: どのような種類のコミュニケーション、もしくは情報をもっと欲しいと思いますか？

question.en: What areas are ahead of schedule?
question.ja_JP: 予定より先に進んでいる部分はどのへんですか？

question.en: Is there anything that’s slowing you down from getting your work done?
question.ja_JP: 仕事を完了するうえで、遅延の原因となっているのはどういった部分ですか？

question.en: Are there any problems or issues that I should know about?
question.ja_JP: 私が知っておくべき課題や問題はありますか？

question.en: What do you think you can do to fix that problem?
question.ja_JP: その問題をあなた自身で解決できると思いますか？

question.en: What could you have done differently?
question.ja_JP: 別の方法だと何ができたでしょうか？

question.en: What worries you? What’s on your mind?
question.ja_JP: なにか不安なことはありあすか？　思うことがあれば教えてもらえますか？

question.en: What areas of your work are you confident about?
question.ja_JP: 仕事で自信のある分野は何ですか？

question.en: What worries you?
question.ja_JP: なにか不安なことはありますか？

question.en: What suggestions do you have?
question.ja_JP: なにか提案はありますか？

question.en: What questions do you have about this project?
question.ja_JP: プロジェクトについてなにか質問はありますか？

question.en: How are you going to approach this?
question.ja_JP: これについてどのようにやろうと思っていますか？

question.en: How are you planning to balance work and personal life this year?
question.ja_JP: 今年のワークライフバランスはどのようにやっていこうと考えていますか？

question.en: What are you doing for yourself outside of work?
question.ja_JP: 仕事以外であなた自身のためにやっていることってありますか？

question.en: Is there anything you’d like to be doing on your own time to relieve stress that you’re not getting to? How can I help you achieve those personal goals?
question.ja_JP: あなたの時間を使ってやりたいけどやれてないストレス軽減方法はありますか？　それをできるようにするために私が手伝えることはありますか？

question.en: What does your ideal weekday look like?
question.ja_JP: あなたの理想的な平日はどのようなものですか？

question.en: How is your workload right now?
question.ja_JP: いまいま忙しすぎてないですか？

question.en: How do you feel about your work/life balance?
question.ja_JP: あなたのワークライフバランスについて、どう感じていますか？

question.en: What, if anything, did you used to do that you find you don’t have time for right now?
question.ja_JP: やろうとおもってたけど時間がない！　という事って今今ありますか？

question.en: What could we change about work that would improve the rest of your life?
question.ja_JP: あなたの人生をよりよいものにするために、仕事で変えるべき部分はありますか？

question.en: Which part of the day do you feel most productive? When do you feel that your energy and focus are at the lowest level? What are the changes that can be made so you can take the best out of a work day?
question.ja_JP: 一日の中でもっとも生産的だと思うのはいつですか？　一番やる気も集中力も無いと感じるのはいつですか？ 仕事で一日を最大限に有効活用するために何を変えればいいと思いますか？

question.en: What were your biggest time wasters or roadblocks last week or the week before?
question.ja_JP: 先週、または先々週でもっとも時間を浪費した、もしくは障害になったものは何ですか？

question.en: What stands in your way?
question.ja_JP: あなたの邪魔になるものは何ですか？

question.en: What was difficult this week? what have you learned?
question.ja_JP: 今週難しかった点は何ですか？　そこから何を学べましたか？

question.en: When was your last vacation?
question.ja_JP: 最後に長期休暇をとったのはいつですか？

question.en: When is your next vacation?
question.ja_JP: 次はいつ長期休暇を取る予定ですか？

question.en: What part of the day do you have the most energy and focus? When do you have the least? What changes could we make to your work schedule to accommodate this?
question.ja_JP: 一日の中でもっとも集中できているとおもうのはいつですか？ 一番集中できていないのはいつですか？　いつでも集中して働けるようにするために勤務スケジュールに変更を加えるとしたらどういったことが良いでしょうか？

question.en: What are 3 things could we do to improve your productivity if money was no object?
question.ja_JP: お金以外で、あなたの生産性を向上させる3つのことを教えて下さい。

question.en: What is an ideal, productive day at work for you? Walk me through the day…
question.ja_JP: あなたにとって最も理想的で生産的な仕事の一日の流れを説明してください。

question.en: What’s an inexpensive thing we could do to improve our office environment?
question.ja_JP: お金をかけずにオフィス環境を良くしようと思ったら、どんなアイデアがありますか？

question.en: What are the biggest time wasters for you each week?
question.ja_JP: あなたが毎週最も時間を使っていることを教えてください。

question.en: What makes you excited and motivated to work on a project?
question.ja_JP: 仕事のプロジェクトで、一番あなたがワクワクしたり、やる気が出ることを教えて下さい。

question.en: When you get stuck on something, what is your process for getting unstuck? Who do you turn to for help?
question.ja_JP: 何かに行き詰まったとき、どうやってそこから抜け出しますか？誰に助けを求めますか？

question.en: What part of your work routine do you find is working best? What area do you want to improve?
question.ja_JP: 仕事における定型のタスクや手続きについて、うまく機能していると思うものはなんですか？どんな部分を改善してほしいと思いますか？

question.en: What do you do when you feel low energy or unmotivated?
question.ja_JP: やる気や気力が下がったとき、どんなことをしますか？

question.en: How can I help…? (be more productive/happier at work/enjoy work more/etc)
question.ja_JP: あなたの仕事の生産性や楽しさを改善するために、なにか私に手助けできることはありますか？

question.en: Is there anything that you’re struggling with?
question.ja_JP: 今なかなか解決できずに困っていることはありますか？

question.en: Is there anything that you need from me?
question.ja_JP: 何か私からあなたに提供できる、必要なものはありますか？

question.en: What is the most important thing we need to discuss today?
question.ja_JP: 今日二人で一番話し合わなければいけないことは何でしょうか。

question.en: What are your most significant accomplishments since we last met?
question.ja_JP: 最後に1on1をしてから今回までの間に、一番大きな成功や成し遂げたことはなんですか？

question.en: What are the most important things you will focus on before we meet next?
question.ja_JP: 次の1on1までに、あなたが取り組むべき最重要課題はなんですか？

question.en: What obstacles are you encountering right now?
question.ja_JP: 今現在直面している困難や障害を教えて下さい。

question.en: How are you feeling about work?
question.ja_JP: 仕事のことをどう感じていますか？

question.en: What about your job is most satisfying for you?
question.ja_JP: 仕事関連のものごとで、最も満足していることは何ですか？

question.en: What about work is frustrating?
question.ja_JP: 仕事関連のものごとでフラストレーションを感じることを教えて下さい。

question.en: If you could change one thing about your job today, what would you change?
question.ja_JP: あなたの仕事についてなにかひとつだけ変えられるとしたら、何を変えますか？
